The paper presents a system for automatic generation of visual blends using structured visual representations and sets of visual relations. This involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for mapping and blending visual elements, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.AI sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with graphics and visualization (cs.GR) as well as computer vision (cs.CV) since it involves the manipulation of visual representations. The paper also discusses the aesthetic quality of the generated blends, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for generating visually interesting and unexpected blends.
